Problem Statement:

The aim of this dataset is to help address the difficult task of detecting the location of large ships in satellite images. Automating this process can be applied to many issues including monitoring port activity levels and supply chain analysis.

In [274]:
#building model

model = Sequential()
#first layer we need to mention input shape
model.add(Conv2D(16,3, padding='same', input_shape=(80,80,3), activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
#add a conv layer followed by maxpooling
# Size of activation layer is 80*80*3=19200

#add a conv layer followed by maxpooling
model.add(Conv2D(32,3,padding='same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))) #20x20

#add a conv layer followed by maxpooling
model.add(Conv2D(64,3, padding='same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))) #10x10

#add a conv layer followed by maxpooling
model.add(Conv2D(32,3, padding='same', activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))) #5x5

#convert feature map in 1d array
model.add(Flatten())
#fully connected layer with 512 neurons
model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))

#final layer
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
#summary
model.summary()

#visualizing the accuracy and loss of train and validation 

train_accuracy=history.history['accuracy']
val_acc=history.history['val_accuracy']
train_loss=history.history['loss']
val_loss=history.history['val_loss']
epoches=list(range(1,16))

plt.figure(figsize=(8,8)) #figure size
plt.subplot(2,1,1)
plt.plot(epoches,train_accuracy,label='train_acc')
plt.plot(epoches,val_acc,label='val_acc')
plt.title('accuracy') #title of the graph
plt.ylabel('accuracy') #label of y-axis
plt.xlabel('epochs') #label of x-axis
plt.legend(loc='lower right') #legend of accuracy graph

plt.figure(figsize=(8,8)) #figure size
plt.subplot(2,1,2)
plt.plot(epoches,train_loss,label='train_loss')
plt.plot(epoches,val_loss,label='val_loss')
plt.title('loss') #title of loss graph
plt.xlabel('epochs') #label for x-axis
plt.ylabel('loss') #label for y-axis
plt.legend() #legend for loss graph
